rComments: Amazing prof! She was able to keep my attention given the COVID circumstances with online school. Not only easy but super interesting. Although I didn't appreciate the proctored exams, increased my stress levels since sometimes I need a break from looking at a screen but I was afraid respondus would say I cheated or something.

Her rating really doesn't do her any justice. By far my easiest class this semester. Interesting lectures but endless amount of documentaries. You're evaluated on 3 homework, weekly quizzes, and a fairly easy 80 MC final. Be sure to keep track of which discussions or homework to do since it is somewhat vague. Sweet and kind lady, no complaints.

Mme Béguet was stern and straight forward for the few times I saw her. I found her assignments to be easy, but it was very confusing since she would cancel assignments with short notice. I ended up not completing most of the given assignments, so I would suggest doing all the work. Lots of reading, but I am very disappointed in this class.

J'aime beaucoup cette prof. Ça se voit qu'elle tient à ses étudiants, surtout à cause du fait que nous sommes tous en ligne. Elle a offert de diminuer les charges de travail quand certains lui ont demandé, et veut que ses élèves réussissent. Ses cours sont très intéressants!

This class is pretty interesting, but not my cup of tea. I found she tried to intimidate students and made her mid terms and exams seem terrible. They are not too bad. Textbook readings are not mandatory, but she tests on all other complementary info. To be honest, I needed a large coffee before every class.

Not a fantastic prof if you aren't fluent in French and don't love anthropology - lectures are fairly heavy. She clearly cares very much about her subject, so if you enjoy antro and are willing to put in a little work, you'll be fine. Two midterms that were very easy (no need to read the textbook); the final exam is all MC, also pretty easy.
Vraiment intéressant ce cours! Ce cours touche plusieurs sphères de la vie et la prof est en mesure de rendre le cours intéressant!

She's very passionate and knowledgeable on her materiel. Textbook is a waste of money, but the books were used in the exam. Attendance is a good idea as she will question you on things not found on the powerpoint. Overall decent class and easy grade. Nothing too negative.

She is very knowledgable and passionate about anthropology. She is a very sweet lately and cracks a few jokes during lectures. The class can be a bit disrespectful to her. An easy credit and would take again. No need for textbook and attendance is pretty optional. Sometimes lectures are boring.

Solid prof, she clearly cares about the subject (obviously, she's an anthropologist). I didn't use the textbook as much, but I'd still recommend doing the readings in case something isn't covered in lecture. She shows videos and other things in class, so make sure to show up.

Found it really easy to pass without reading the textbook, but definitely needed to read one of the two other books. A lot of the information is spoken: she just has main ideas on powerpoint slides. Easy to understand and doesn't try to trick you or overload on the information. Assignments were not super easy nor super hard.

Très gentille et passionnée de son sujet. Parfois, il arrive que le contenu du cours devienne complexe et confisant mais elle est très ouverte au question. Elle ajoute aussi toujours ses powerpoint sur brightspace d'avance ce qui est super.

I took this class as an elective. Prof Béguet isn't my cup of tea, she is very dry/boring. Good thing is that all of her powerpoints are online with all the information needed. One take home midterm, one MC midterm & take home final. I bought the books and never used them. Barely went to class and got a good grade. Overall, easy A but boring prof.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: So in case you still don't know she went to Borneo and will talk about it all the time! Pretty easy assignments ! Don't bother buying the textbooks you don't need them to pass! Will only let you leave 5 mins before the class ends! In overall, she did not make a good impression but her class is easy credits and an easy A!

She is a passionate anthropologist, but treat the class like we are in high school, don't expect her to let you off before the hour and a half is done. She went to Borneo and you will KNOW ABOUT IT. Apart from this the class is easy if you are already a social science student. Don't bother buying the text book + assignments are 2 take home 5pages

The teacher is amazing and really passionate about what she is teaching! Her class is very interesting because when she brings up a subject, she gives examples about her own experiences in Borneo. If it wasn't for her I probably wouldn't have love this class that much.

C'est probablement une des mes prof préférées de tout mon parcours scolaire. Elle m'a tellement fait aimé l'anthropologie que j'ai décidé d'étudier dans ce domaine. Les cours sont vraiment intéressants si vous êtes du genre à tripper sur tout ce qui est culturel, des débats sur la culture et ses composants! Exemples de terrain!!!
This course felt like the type you take in high school for an easy mark. Prof was decent and really passionate about anthropology, but the material was painfully simple. Meh.

The readings are sort of integrated into the lectures. She'd go on a tangent almost every class, making us late for other classes. The essay and the final exam is easy to write because she gives you the criteria beforehand. She was very passionate about her stuff. Her anecdotes from her research was pretty cool.

She knows her subject very well but rambles a lot outside of the subject. She doesnt post the powerpoints (that are essential to the exams) on blackboard so you have to write everything down quickly while she talks. The exam and assignment were easy.

WORST. PROF. EVER. Very French so struggles to make herself sound clear. Not online except to post useless links to readings shes already making us buy. Treats everyone like theyre on a direct path to becomin an anthropologist and has no respect for family emergencies, for which I had to drop out because she failed me for missing 1 small assignment

Quite disorganized, but seems to care a lot about anthropology. One thing I didn't appreciate was when she outwardly accused some of the students of not paying attention just because we were sitting back (just needed to be close to an outlet in order to take notes on my laptop)  Turned me off to her as a prof. Pretty rude.

This was my least favourite class and professor in university. Prof. Beguet is uninteresting, disorganized and does not provide explanations or help. Assignments are not difficult, yet marked hard. PowerPoints are not posted online. Do not recommend this course or professor.

Prof Béguet is very knowledgeable, but gets lost in her tangeants. Her powerpoints also don't follow her presentation. Things get more interesting as the class evolves. I could reccomend to someone with a genuine interest in anthropology.

Véronique donne des présentations intéressantes mais les powerpoints qu'elle utilise ne sont pas publiés sur Blackboard. Elle pars souvent sur des tangentes mais son examen final est une dissertation faite à la maison donc du niaisage dans le cours est acceptable. Ces évaluations sont assez simples. Les lectures dans le manuel sont un peu inutiles.

"Psychologie de la religion" is a very misleading name for the course. She taught more about psychologist thought over history with a focus on the unconscious and out of body experiences. She is an anthropologist by nature, not a psychologist which influences the lens in which she teaches. She doesn't share her slides online, exams were easy.

She talks on and on and loses track of her thought multiple times trying to explain one thing.  Didn't come to see my partner and I to help us with our project, so we had to stay after the 7-10pm class.  She's a big power tripper and is discriminating person.  If you're not part of people she likes, good luck receiving help.
This teacher adores anthropology but she's confusing at times. She required us to buy 3 textbooks to only read a few chapters from each book...

Her lectures were very unclear and she kind of jumped around a lot... Her lecture slides almost never seemed to be relative to what she was talking about and she never really answered questions clearly. The only good thing was that her assignments were super easy. Ended up dropping the class - not because it was hard, but how bad she was.

She was unclear during her lectures and rambled for the majority of the time. Honestly, if it weren't for the TA, I don't know if I would have passed. She was very rude and condescending to students whether for cellphone use, or correcting them after oral presentation. Everyone wrote at least an entire page of negative feedback during course evals.

This is a real boring class ever the prof has the knowledge but she is not a teacher. no black board note, very unorganized, I abandon this class in the end of this  semester. I will not recommend any one to take class with this prof. no note and require long memorization in exam. sever correction.

Nice lady. Seems very knowledgeable & experienced in her field & her personal experiences are interesting but not the best prof in terms of teaching. Very unorganized & doesn't have much control over the class. Made me lose interest in this subject which I loved. Easy-ish grader, gives bonus points if you give quality work. Staying motivated is key

As a french immersion student I went into this class not sure what to expect. Needless to say I'm not even halfway through the semester and I'm already afraid of failing the class. Although her clarity is good, she doesn't use any slides and so taking notes is difficult for me. I am surviving off of the textbook only.
Very all over the place! I had a hard time following her train of thought. The exam and midterm were easy! She also gives surprise quizzes.

ANT1501 - Painfully boring, unorganized and hardly used virtual campus. Her train of thought is difficult - if not impossible - to follow and she never uses slideshows (if she does they are jam-packed). The midterm and final were super easy (with extremely minimal study time), and she gives two 'pop quizzes', one before and one after the midterm.

Worst class this semester. Very dull, unorganized, no order in what she's talking about, treats us like kids, and her grading is all over the place (though she gives a lot of random bonus points) watch out for surprise quizzes...
She is awesome!
Absolutely brutal. Completely unorganized and probably the worst course I took my first year. Made me drop my double major in Sociology and Anthropology, to just sociology.
